        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the mince has started to brown, add your <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong>, <strong>honey</strong>, <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong>, <strong>half </strong>your <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), and <strong>half</strong> your <strong>soy sauce </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for 4-5 min or until the mince has caramelised and is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>sticky beef</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
